\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Schemes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A locally ringed space 
\begin_inset Formula $(X,\mathcal{O}_{X})$
\end_inset

 is called an 
\series bold
affine scheme 
\series default
if there exists a ring 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $(X,\mathcal{O}_{X})$
\end_inset

 is isomorphic to 
\begin_inset Formula $(\text{Spec }A,\mathcal{O}_{\text{Spec }A})$
\end_inset

 A 
\series bold
morphism 
\series default
of affine schemes is a morphism of locally ringed spaces.
 We obtain the category of affine schemes which we denote by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{Aff}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

A 
\series bold
scheme 
\series default
is a locally ringed space 
\begin_inset Formula $(X,\mathcal{O}_{X})$
\end_inset

 which admits an open covering 
\begin_inset Formula $X=\bigcup_{i\in I}U_{i}$
\end_inset

 such that all locally ringed spaces 
\begin_inset Formula $(U_{i},\mathcal{O}_{X|U_{i}})$
\end_inset

 are affine schemes.
 A 
\series bold
morphism
\series default
 of schemes is a morphism of locally ringed spaces.
 We obtain the category of schemes which we will denote by 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{Sch}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

